      %h3 Headers + Type Examples
      %hr
      %h1 Five Pillars
      %p 
        Although Wikipedia is the encyclopedia anyone can edit, that doesn't mean that everyone can edit it independently. But good articles aren’t written by making chaotic, random edits. In fact, a lot goes on behind the scenes of every page! When volunteers work on an article, they’re working within a set of principles, often called the Five Pillars.
      .bg-color.my1
        .card-block
          .card-block__header
            %h2.card-block__title Welcome to Wikipedia
            .icon-card
              %img{src: "http://i.imgsafe.org/bfd7bcf.png", alt: ""}/
          .card-block__content
            %p.secondary
              Basic mechanics of editing Wikipedia pages and communicating with others. Lorem ipsum does el ipsum lorenm la.
      .toc
        .title
          %p.left.toc__header Table of Contents
          %p.right.toc__header 20 Pages
        .scroll-wrap
          .module__preview
          %ol
            %li.module__item
              .toc__item-header Item Header
              %p.tertiary Brief description of what will be covered on this slide. Lorem ipsum dolor es qua.
